race.comment: JADE DIVISION (1) backs up seven days after a convincing win over this distance at Mudgee. Getting up in the weights but has obviously thrived since last Saturday's run and can get the job done again. MERRY MORE (10) returned from a spell with a respectable third over 1200m at Grenfell last start. Looking for at least this trip now so another big run looks on the cards. PAHANG (5) worked home fairly but was never a threat in a $50k picnic race over this distance at Dubbo recently. Fitter for two runs back from a spell and gets all the favours out of the inside gate. GUSTAV (2) closed well to get up for third in a Class 2 over 1150m at Leeton last start. Serious contender in this far easier assignment. FREAKY FRIDAY (11) next best in a race with a long tail.
